The paper discusses a new ensemble approach for outlier detection in multi-dimensional point data, which involves reducing error through both bias and variance. This work is related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories as they cover the theoretical and practical aspects of machine learning algorithms. cs.DM (Data Mining) is also a likely category as it deals with the process of discovering patterns in large datasets. cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as it covers the storage, retrieval, and management of large datasets. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as outlier detection is often used in security applications.
